 Following the 40th birthday celebration of Nigerian billionaire Emeka Okonkwo, also known as E-money, Nigerian media personality Daddy Freeze has given an important advice to ‘Last Born.’ Many Nigerian celebrities and socialites attend E-money’s 40th birthday celebration in Lagos this weekend. READ MORE: Obi Cubana, Daddy Freeze Accompany Former Pure Water Hawker To Receive Admission Letter According to Daddy Freeze, E-money’s sister informed him that the billionaire businessman is his family’s last born, defying the Nigerian tradition of many last borns. He went on to say that E money’s existence should inspire every new born to quit relying on hand-me-downs from older siblings. See post below:   A post shared by FRZ (@daddyfreeze)  